 28 n2i.browser.opera = /opera/i.test(navigator.userAgent);
 29 n2i.browser.msie = !n2i.browser.opera && /MSIE/.test(navigator.userAgent);
 30 n2i.browser.msie6 = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('MSIE 6')!==-1;
 31 n2i.browser.msie7 = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('MSIE 7')!==-1;
 32 n2i.browser.msie8 = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('MSIE 8')!==-1;
 33 n2i.browser.webkit = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('WebKit')!==-1;
 34 n2i.browser.safari = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('Safari')!==-1;
 35 n2i.browser.webkitVersion = null;
 36 n2i.browser.gecko = !n2i.browser.webkit && navigator.userAgent.indexOf('Gecko')!=-1;

 48 		console.log(obj);
 49 	} catch (ignore) {};

 52 /** Make a string camelized */
 53 n2i.camelize = function(str) {
 54 	if (str.indexOf('-')==-1) {return str}
 55     var oStringList = str.split('-');
 56 
 57     var camelizedString = str.indexOf('-') == 0
 58       ? oStringList[0].charAt(0).toUpperCase() + oStringList[0].substring(1)
 59       : oStringList[0];
 60 
 61     for (var i = 1, len = oStringList.length; i < len; i++) {
 62       var s = oStringList[i];
 63       camelizedString += s.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + s.substring(1);
 64     }
 65 
 66     return camelizedString;
 67 }

 69 /** Override the properties on the first argument with properties from the last object */
 70 n2i.override = function(original,subject) {
 71 	if (subject) {
 72 		for (prop in subject) {
 73 			original[prop] = subject[prop];
 74 		}
 75 	}
 76 	return original;
 77 }

 79 n2i.wrap = function(str) {
 80 	if (str===null || str===undefined) {
 81 		return '';
 82 	}
 83 	return str.split('').join("\u200B");
 84 }

 86 /** Trim whitespace including unicode chars */
 87 n2i.trim = function(str) {
 88 	if (!str) return str;
 89 	return str.replace(/^[\s\x0b\xa0\u2000\u2001\u2002\u2003\u2004\u2005\u2006\u2007\u2008\u2009\u200a\u200b\u2028\u2029\u3000]+|[\s\x0b\xa0\u2000\u2001\u2002\u2003\u2004\u2005\u2006\u2007\u2008\u2009\u200a\u200b\u2028\u2029\u3000]+$/g, '');
 90 }

 92 /** Escape the html in a string */
 93 n2i.escapeHTML = function(str) {
 94    	return document.createElement('div').appendChild(document.createTextNode(str)).innerHTML;
 95 }

 97 n2i.escape = function(str) {
 98 	if (!n2i.isDefined(str)) {return ''};
 99 	return str.replace(/&/g,'&').
100 		replace(/>/g,'>').
101 		replace(/</g,'<').
102 		replace(/"/g,'"')
103 }

105 /** Checks if a string has characters */
106 n2i.isEmpty = n2i.isBlank = function(str) {
107 	if (str===null || typeof(str)==='undefined' || str==='') return true;
108 	return typeof(str)=='string' && n2i.trim(str).length==0;
109 }

111 /** Checks that an object is not null or undefined */
112 n2i.isDefined = function(obj) {
113 	return obj!==null && typeof(obj)!=='undefined';
114 }

116 n2i.isArray = function(obj) {
117 	if (obj.constructor == Array) {
118 		return true;
119 	} else {
120 		return Object.prototype.toString.call(obj) === '[object Array]';
121 	}
122 }

124 n2i.inArray = function(arr,value) {
125 	for (var i=0; i < arr.length; i++) {
126 		if (arr[i]==value) {
127 			return true;
128 		}
129 	};
130 	return false;
131 }
132 
133 n2i.indexInArray = function(arr,value) {
134 	for (var i=0; i < arr.length; i++) {
135 		if (arr[i]==value) {
136 			return i;
137 		}
138 	};
139 	return -1;
140 }

142 n2i.each = function(items,func) {
143 	if (n2i.isArray(items)) {		
144 		for (var i=0; i < items.length; i++) {
145 			func(items[i],i);
146 		};
147 	} else {
148 		for (key in items) {
149 			func(key,items[key]);
150 		}
151 	}
152 }

154 /**
155  * Converts a string to an int if it is only digits, otherwise remains a string
156  */
157 n2i.intOrString = function(str) {
158 	if (n2i.isDefined(str)) {
159 		var result = /[0-9]+/.exec(str);
160 		if (result!==null && result[0]==str) {
161 			if (parseInt(str,10)==str) {
162 				return parseInt(str,10);
163 			}
164 		}
165 	}
166 	return str;
167 }
168 
169 n2i.flipInArray = function(arr,value) {
170 	if (n2i.inArray(arr,value)) {
171 		n2i.removeFromArray(arr,value);
172 	} else {
173 		arr.push(value);
174 	}
175 }
176 
177 n2i.removeFromArray = function(arr,value) {
178 	for (var i = arr.length - 1; i >= 0; i--){
179 		if (arr[i]==value) {
180 			arr.splice(i,1);
181 		}
182 	};
183 }
184 
185 n2i.addToArray = function(arr,value) {
186 	if (value.constructor==Array) {
187 		for (var i=0; i < value.length; i++) {
188 			if (!n2i.inArray(arr,value[i])) {
189 				arr.push(value);
190 			}
191 		};
192 	} else {
193 		if (!n2i.inArray(arr,value)) {
194 			arr.push(value);
195 		}
196 	}
197 }
198 
199 n2i.toIntArray = function(str) {
200 	var array = str.split(',');
201 	for (var i = array.length - 1; i >= 0; i--){
202 		array[i] = parseInt(array[i]);
203 	};
204 	return array;
205 }

207 n2i.scrollTo = function(element) {
208 	element = $(element);
209 	if (element) {
210 		var pos = element.cumulativeOffset();
211 		window.scrollTo(pos.left, pos.top-50);
212 	}
213 }

217 /** @namespace */
218 n2i.dom = {
219 	isElement : function(n,name) {
220 		return n.nodeType==n2i.ELEMENT_NODE && (name===undefined ? true : n.nodeName.toLowerCase()==name);
221 	},
222 	isDefinedText : function(node) {
223 		return node.nodeType==n2i.TEXT_NODE && node.nodeValue.length>0;
224 	},
225 	addText : function(node,text) {
226 		node.appendChild(document.createTextNode(text));
227 	},
228 	clear : function(node) {
229 		var children = node.childNodes;
230 		for (var i = children.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
231 			children[i].parentNode.removeChild(children[i]);
232 		};
233 	},
234 	remove : function(node) {
235 		if (node.parentNode) {
236 			node.parentNode.removeChild(node);
237 		}
238 	},
239 	replaceHTML : function(node,html) {
240 		node = n2i.get(node);
241 		node.innerHTML=html;
242 	},
243 	runScripts : function(node) {
244 		var scripts = node.getElementsByTagName('script');
245 		for (var i=0; i < scripts.length; i++) {
246 			eval(scripts[i].innerHTML);
247 		}
248 	},
249 	setText : function(node,text) {
250 		var c = node.childNodes;
251 		var updated = false;
252 		for (var i=0; i < c.length; i++) {
253 			if (!updated && node.nodeType==n2i.TEXT_NODE) {
254 				node.nodeValue=text;
255 				updated = true;
256 			} else {
257 				node.removeChild(c[i]);
258 			}
259 		}
260 		if (!updated) {
261 			n2i.dom.addText(node,text);
262 		}
263 	},
264 	getText : function(node) {
265 		var txt = '';
266 		var c = node.childNodes;
267 		for (var i=0; i < c.length; i++) {
268 			if (c[i].nodeType==n2i.TEXT_NODE && c[i].nodeValue!=null) {
269 				txt+=c[i].nodeValue;
270 			} else if (c[i].nodeType==n2i.ELEMENT_NODE) {
271 				txt+=n2i.dom.getNodeText(c[i]);
272 			}
273 		};
274 		return txt;
275 	},
276 	isVisible : function(node) {
277 		while (node) {
278 			if (node.style && (n2i.getStyle(node,'display')==='none' || n2i.getStyle(node,'visibility')==='hidden')) {
279 				return false;
280 			}
281 			node = node.parentNode;
282 		}
283 		return true;
284 	}
285 }

287 n2i.form = {
288 	getValues : function(node) {
289 		var params = {};
290 		var inputs = node.getElementsByTagName('input');
291 		for (var i=0; i < inputs.length; i++) {
292 			if (n2i.isDefined(inputs[i].name)) {
293 				params[inputs[i].name] = inputs[i].value;
294 			}
295 		};
296 		return params;
297 	}
298 }

300 n2i.get = function(str) {
301 	if (typeof(str)=='string') {
302 		return document.getElementById(str);
303 	}
304 	return str;

307 n2i.getChildren = function(node) {
308 	var children = [];
309 	var x = node.childNodes;
310 	for (var i=0; i < x.length; i++) {
311 		if (n2i.dom.isElement(x[i])) {
312 			children.push(x[i]);
313 		}
314 	};
315 	return children;

318 n2i.firstByClass = function(parentElement,className,tag) {
319 	var children = (n2i.get(parentElement) || document.body).getElementsByTagName(tag || '*');
320 	for (var i=0;i<children.length;i++) {
321 		if (n2i.hasClass(children[i],className)) {
322 			return children[i];
323 		}
324 	}
325 	return null;
326 }
327 
328 n2i.byClass = function(parentElement,className,tag) {
329 	var children = (n2i.get(parentElement) || document.body).getElementsByTagName(tag || '*');
330 	var out = [];
331 	for (var i=0;i<children.length;i++) {
332 		if (n2i.hasClass(children[i],className)) {
333 			out[out.length]=children[i];
334 		}
335 	}
336 	return out;
337 }
338 
339 n2i.firstByTag = function(parentElement,tag) {
340 	var children = (n2i.get(parentElement) || document.body).getElementsByTagName(tag);
341 	return children[0];
342 }
343 
344 n2i.build = function(tag,options) {
345 	var e = document.createElement(tag);
346 	if (options) {
347 		for (prop in options) {
348 			if (prop=='text') {
349 				e.appendChild(document.createTextNode(options.text));
350 			} else if (prop=='html') {
351 				e.innerHTML=options.html;
352 			} else if (prop=='parent') {
353 				options.parent.appendChild(e);
354 			} else if (prop=='className') {
355 				e.className=options.className;
356 			} else if (prop=='class') {
357 				e.className=options['class'];
358 			} else if (n2i.isDefined(options[prop])) {
359 				e.setAttribute(prop,options[prop]);
360 			}
361 		}
362 	}
363 	return e;
364 }
365 
366 n2i.getAncestors = function(element) {
367 	var ancestors = [];
368 	var parent = element.parentNode;
369 	while (parent) {
370 		ancestors[ancestors.length] = parent;
371 		parent = parent.parentNode;
372 	}
373 	return ancestors;
374 }

376 n2i.getNext = function(element) {
377 	if (!element) {
378 		return null;
379 	}
380 	if (!element.nextSibling) {
381 		return null;
382 	}
383 	var next = element.nextSibling;
384 	while (next && next.nodeType!=1) {
385 		next = next.nextSibling;
386 	}
387     return next;
388 }
389 
390 n2i.getAllNext = function(element) {
391 	var elements = [];
392 	var next = n2i.getNext(element);
393 	while (next) {
394 		elements.push(next);
395 		next = n2i.getNext(next);
396 	}
397 	return elements;
398 }

400 n2i.getTop = function(element) {
401     element = n2i.get(element);
402 	if (element) {
403 		var yPos = element.offsetTop;
404 		var tempEl = element.offsetParent;
405 		while (tempEl != null) {
406 			yPos += tempEl.offsetTop;
407 			tempEl = tempEl.offsetParent;
408 		}
409 		return yPos;
410 	}
411 	else return 0;
412 }
413 
414 n2i.getLeft = function(element) {
415     element = n2i.get(element);
416 	if (element) {
417 		var xPos = element.offsetLeft;
418 		var tempEl = element.offsetParent;
419 		while (tempEl != null) {
420 			xPos += tempEl.offsetLeft;
421 			tempEl = tempEl.offsetParent;
422 		}
423 		return xPos;
424 	}
425 	else return 0;
426 }
427 
428 n2i.getPosition = function(element) {
429 	return {
430 		left : n2i.getLeft(element),
431 		top : n2i.getTop(element)
432 	}
433 }

437 n2i.hasClass = function(element, className) {
438 	element = n2i.get(element);
439 	if (!element || !element.className) {
440 		return false
441 	}
442 	var a = element.className.split(/\s+/);
443 	for (var i = 0; i < a.length; i++) {
444 		if (a[i] == className) {
445 			return true;
446 		}
447 	}
448 	return false;
449 }
450 
451 n2i.addClass = function(element, className) {
452     element = n2i.get(element);
453 	if (!element) {return};
454 	
455     n2i.removeClass(element, className);
456     element.className += ' ' + className;
457 }
458 
459 n2i.removeClass = function(element, className) {
460 	element = n2i.get(element);
461 	if (!element) {return};
462 
463 	var newClassName = '';
464 	var a = element.className.split(/\s+/);
465 	for (var i = 0; i < a.length; i++) {
466 		if (a[i] != className) {
467 			if (i > 0) {
468 				newClassName += ' ';				
469 			}
470 			newClassName += a[i];
471 		}
472 	}
473 	element.className = newClassName;
474 }
475 
476 n2i.toggleClass = function(element,className) {
477 	if (n2i.hasClass(element,className)) {
478 		n2i.removeClass(element,className);
479 	} else {
480 		n2i.addClass(element,className);
481 	}
482 }
483 
484 n2i.setClass = function(element,className,add) {
485 	if (add) {
486 		n2i.addClass(element,className);
487 	} else {
488 		n2i.removeClass(element,className);
489 	}
490 }

503 n2i.listen = function(el,type,listener,useCapture) {
504 	el = n2i.get(el);
505 	if(document.addEventListener) {
506 		el.addEventListener(type,listener,useCapture ? true : false);
507 	} else {
508 		el.attachEvent('on'+type, listener);
509 	}
510 }
511 
512 n2i.unListen = function(el,type,listener,useCapture) {
513 	el = n2i.get(el);
514 	if(document.removeEventListener) {
515 		el.removeEventListener(type,listener,useCapture ? true : false);
516 	} else {
517 		el.detachEvent('on'+type, listener);
518 	}
519 }

521 n2i.event = function(event) {
522 	return new n2i.Event();
523 }
524 
525 n2i.Event = function(event) {
526 	this.event = event = event || window.event;
527 	this.element = event.target ? event.target : event.srcElement;
528 	this.shiftKey = event.shiftKey;
529 	this.returnKey = event.keyCode==13;
530 	this.escapeKey = event.keyCode==27;
531 	this.spaceKey = event.keyCode==32;
532 	this.upKey = event.keyCode==38;
533 	this.downKey = event.keyCode==40;
534 	this.leftKey = event.keyCode==37;
535 	this.rightKey = event.keyCode==39;
536 	this.keyCode = event.keyCode;
537 }
538 
539 n2i.Event.prototype = {
540 	left : function() {
541 	    var left = 0;
542 		if (this.event) {
543 		    if (this.event.pageX) {
544 			    left = this.event.pageX;
545 		    } else if (this.event.clientX) {
546 			    left = this.event.clientX + document.body.scrollLeft;
547 		    }
548 		}
549 	    return left;
550 	},
551 	getLeft : function() {
552 		return this.left();
553 	},
554 	top : function() {
555 	    var top = 0;
556 		if (this.event) {
557 		    if (this.event.pageY) {
558 			    top = this.event.pageY;
559 		    } else if (this.event.clientY) {
560 			    top = this.event.clientY + document.body.scrollTop;
561 		    }
562 		}
563 	    return top;
564 	},
565 	getTop : function() {
566 		return this.top();
567 	},
568 	getElement : function() {
569 		return this.element;
570 	},
571 	findByClass : function(cls) {
572 		var parent = this.element;
573 		while (parent) {
574 			if (n2i.hasClass(parent,cls)) {
575 				return parent;
576 			}
577 			parent = parent.parentNode;
578 		}
579 		return null;
580 	},
581 	findByTag : function(tag) {
582 		var parent = this.element;
583 		while (parent) {
584 			if (parent.tagName.toLowerCase()==tag) {
585 				return parent;
586 			}
587 			parent = parent.parentNode;
588 		}
589 		return null;
590 	},
591 
592 	stop : function() {
593 		n2i.stop(this.event);
594 	}
595 }
596 
597 n2i.stop = function(e) {
598 	if (!e) {e = window.event};
599 	if (e.stopPropagation) {e.stopPropagation()};
600 	if (e.preventDefault) {e.preventDefault()};
601 	e.cancelBubble = true;
602     e.stopped = true;
603 }
604 
605 n2i.onReady = function(delegate) {
606 	if(window.addEventListener) {
607 		window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded',delegate);
608 	}
609 	else if(typeof document.addEventListener != 'undefined')
610 	{
611 		//.. opera 7
612 		document.addEventListener('load', delegate, false);
613 	}
614 	else if(typeof window.attachEvent != 'undefined')
615 	{
616 		//.. win/ie
617 		window.attachEvent('onload', delegate);
618 	}
619 
620 	//** remove this condition to degrade older browsers
621 	else
622 	{
623 		//.. mac/ie5 and anything else that gets this far
624 	
625 		//if there's an existing onload function
626 		if(typeof window.onload == 'function')
627 		{
628 			//store it
629 			var existing = window.onload;
630 		
631 			//add new onload handler
632 			window.onload = function()
633 			{
634 				//call existing onload function
635 				existing();
636 			
637 				//call delegate onload function
638 				delegate();
639 			};
640 		}
641 		else
642 		{
643 			//setup onload function
644 			window.onload = delegate;
645 		}
646 	}
647 }

649 // Ajax //
650 
651 n2i.request = function(options) {
652 	options = n2i.override({method:'POST',async:true},options);
653 	var transport = n2i.request.createTransport();
654 	var self = this;
655 	transport.onreadystatechange = function() {
656 		try {
657 			if (transport.readyState == 4) {
658 				if (transport.status == 200 && options.onSuccess) {
659 					options.onSuccess(transport);
660 				} else if (options.onFailure) {
661 					options.onFailure(transport);
662 				}
663 			}
664 		} catch (e) {
665 			if (options.onException) {
666 				options.onException(e,transport)
667 			} else {
668 				throw e;
669 			}
670 		}
671 	};
672 	var method = options.method.toUpperCase();
673 	transport.open(method, options.url, options.async);
674 	var parameters = null;
675 	var body = '';
676     if (method=='POST' && options.parameters) {
677 		body = n2i.request.buildPostBody(options.parameters);
678 		transport.setRequestHeader("Content-type", "application/x-www-form-urlencoded; charset=utf-8");
679 		//transport.setRequestHeader("Content-length", body.length);
680 		//transport.setRequestHeader("Connection", "close");
681 	}
682 	transport.send(body);
683 }
684 
685 n2i.request.buildPostBody = function(parameters) {
686 	if (!parameters) return null;
687 	var output = '';
688 	for (param in parameters) {
689 		if (output.length>0) output+='&';
690 		output+=encodeURIComponent(param)+'=';
691 		if (parameters[param]!==undefined && parameters[param]!==null) {
692 			output+=encodeURIComponent(parameters[param]);
693 		}
694 	}
695 	return output;
696 }
697 
698 n2i.request.createTransport = function() {
699 	try {
700 		if (window.XMLHttpRequest) {
701 			var req = new XMLHttpRequest();
702 			if (req.readyState == null) {
703 				req.readyState = 1;
704 				req.addEventListener("load", function () {
705 					req.readyState = 4;
706 					if (typeof req.onreadystatechange == "function")
707 						req.onreadystatechange();
708 				}, false);
709 			}
710 			return req;
711 		}
712 		else if (window.ActiveXObject) {
713 			return n2i.request.getActiveX();
714 		} else {
715 			// Could not create transport
716 			this.delegate.onError(this);
717 		}
718 	}
719 	catch (ex) {
720 		if (this.delegate.onError) {
721 			this.delegate.onError(this,ex);
722 		}
723 	}
724 }
725 
726 n2i.request.getActiveX = function() {
727 	var prefixes = ["MSXML2", "Microsoft", "MSXML", "MSXML3"];
728 	var o;
729 	for (var i = 0; i < prefixes.length; i++) {
730 		try {
731 			// try to create the objects
732 			o = new ActiveXObject(prefixes[i] + ".XmlHttp");
733 			return o;
734 		}
735 		catch (ex) {};
736 	}
737 	
738 	throw new Error("Could not find an installed XML parser");
739 }

741 ///////////////////// Style ///////////////////
742 
743 n2i.getStyle = function(element, style) {
744 	element = n2i.get(element);
745 	var cameled = n2i.camelize(style);
746 	var value = element.style[cameled];
747 	if (!value) {
748 		if (document.defaultView && document.defaultView.getComputedStyle) {
749 			var css = document.defaultView.getComputedStyle(element, null);
750 			value = css ? css.getPropertyValue(style) : null;
751 		} else if (element.currentStyle) {
752 			value = element.currentStyle[cameled];
753 		}
754 	}
755 	if (window.opera && ['left', 'top', 'right', 'bottom'].include(style)) {
756 		if (n2i.getStyle(element, 'position') == 'static') value = 'auto';
757 	}
758 	return value == 'auto' ? null : value;
759 }
760 
761 n2i.setOpacity = function(element,opacity) {
762 	if (n2i.browser.msie) {
763 		if (opacity==1) {
764 			element.style['filter']=null;
765 		} else {
766 			element.style['filter']='alpha(opacity='+(opacity*100)+')';
767 		}
768 	} else {
769 		element.style['opacity']=opacity;
770 	}
771 }
772 
773 n2i.setStyle = function(element,styles) {
774 	for (style in styles) {
775 		if (style==='opacity') {
776 			n2i.setOpacity(element,styles[style]);
777 		} else {
778 			element.style[style] = styles[style];
779 		}
780 	}
781 }
782 
783 n2i.copyStyle = function(source,target,styles) {
784 	for (var i=0; i < styles.length; i++) {
785 		var s = styles[i];
786 		var r = n2i.getStyle(source,s);
787 		if (r) {
788 			target.style[s] = r;
789 		}
790 	};
791 }

924 n2i.getDocumentHeight = function() {
925 	if (n2i.browser.msie6) {
926 		// In IE6 check the children too
927 		var max = Math.max(document.body.clientHeight,document.documentElement.clientHeight,document.documentElement.scrollHeight);
928 		$(document.body).childElements().each(function(node) {
929 			max = Math.max(max,node.getHeight());
930 		});
931 		return max;
932 	}
933 	if (window.scrollMaxY && window.innerHeight) {
934 		return window.scrollMaxY+window.innerHeight;
935 	} else {
936 		return Math.max(document.body.clientHeight,document.documentElement.clientHeight,document.documentElement.scrollHeight);

940 //////////////////////////// Placement /////////////////////////
941 
942 n2i.place = function(options) {
943 	var left=0,top=0;
944 	var trgt = options.target.element;
945 	var trgtPos = {left:n2i.getLeft(trgt),top:n2i.getTop(trgt)};
946 	left = trgtPos.left+trgt.clientWidth*options.target.horizontal;
947 	top = trgtPos.top+trgt.clientHeight*options.target.vertical;
948 	
949 	var src = options.source.element;
950 	left-=src.clientWidth*options.source.horizontal;
951 	top-=src.clientHeight*options.source.vertical;
952 	
953 	var src = options.source.element;
954 	src.style.top=top+'px';
955 	src.style.left=left+'px';
956 }

958 //////////////////////////// Preloader /////////////////////////
959 
960 /** @constructor */
961 n2i.Preloader = function(options) {
962 	this.options = options || {};
963 	this.delegate = {};
964 	this.images = [];
965 	this.loaded = 0;
966 }
967 
968 n2i.Preloader.prototype = {
969 	addImages : function(imageOrImages) {
970 		if (typeof(imageOrImages)=='object') {
971 			for (var i=0; i < imageOrImages.length; i++) {
972 				this.images.push(imageOrImages[i]);
973 			};
974 		} else {
975 			this.images.push(imageOrImages);
976 		}
977 	},
978 	setDelegate : function(d) {
979 		this.delegate = d;
980 	},
981 	load : function(startIndex) {
982 		startIndex = startIndex || 0;
983 		var self = this;
984 		this.obs = [];
985 		for (var i=startIndex; i < this.images.length+startIndex; i++) {
986 			var index=i;
987 			if (index>=this.images.length) {
988 				index = index-this.images.length;
989 			}
990 			var img = new Image();
991 			img.n2iPreloaderIndex = index;
992 			img.onload = function() {self.imageChanged(this.n2iPreloaderIndex,'imageDidLoad')};
993 			img.onerror = function() {self.imageChanged(this.n2iPreloaderIndex,'imageDidGiveError')};
994 			img.onabort = function() {self.imageChanged(this.n2iPreloaderIndex,'imageDidAbort')};
995 			img.src = (this.options.context ? this.options.context : '')+this.images[index];
996 			this.obs.push(img);
997 		};
998 	},
999 	imageChanged : function(index,method) {
1000 		this.loaded++;
1001 		if (this.delegate[method]) {
1002 			this.delegate[method](this.loaded,this.images.length,index);
1003 		}
1004 		if (this.loaded==this.images.length && this.delegate.allImagesDidLoad) {
1005 			this.delegate.allImagesDidLoad();
1006 		}
1007 	}
1008 }

1010 /* @namespace */
1011 n2i.cookie = {
1012 	set : function(name,value,days) {
1013 		if (days) {
1014 			var date = new Date();
1015 			date.setTime(date.getTime()+(days*24*60*60*1000));
1016 			var expires = "; expires="+date.toGMTString();
1017 		}
1018 		else var expires = "";
1019 		document.cookie = name+"="+value+expires+"; path=/";
1020 	},
1021 	get : function(name) {
1022 		var nameEQ = name + "=";
1023 		var ca = document.cookie.split(';');
1024 		for(var i=0;i < ca.length;i++) {
1025 			var c = ca[i];
1026 			while (c.charAt(0)==' ') c = c.substring(1,c.length);
1027 			if (c.indexOf(nameEQ) == 0) return c.substring(nameEQ.length,c.length);
1028 		}
1029 		return null;
1030 	},
1031 	clear : function(name) {
1032 		this.set(name,"",-1);
1033 	}
1034 }

1042 n2i.URL.prototype = {
1043 	addParameter : function(key,value) {
1044 		this.url+=this.url.indexOf('?')!=-1 ? '&' : '?';
1045 		this.url+=key+'='+(n2i.isDefined(value) ? value : '');

1052 /* @namespace */
1053 n2i.location = {
1054 	getParameter : function(name) {
1055 		var parms = n2i.location.getParameters();
1056 		for (var i=0; i < parms.length; i++) {
1057 			if (parms[i].name==name) {
1058 				return parms[i].value;
1059 			}
1060 		};
1061 		return null;
1062 	},
1063 	setParameter : function(name,value) {
1064 		var parms = n2i.location.getParameters();
1065 		var found = false;
1066 		for (var i=0; i < parms.length; i++) {
1067 			if (parms[i].name==name) {
1068 				parms[i].value=value;
1069 				found=true;
1070 				break;
1071 			}
1072 		};
1073 		if (!found) {
1074 			parms.push({name:name,value:value});
1075 		}
1076 		n2i.location.setParameters(parms);
1077 	},
1078 	hasHash : function(name) {
1079 		var h = document.location.hash;
1080 		if (h!=='') {
1081 			return h=='#'+name;
1082 		}
1083 		return false;
1084 	},
1085 	getHashParameter : function(name) {
1086 		var h = document.location.hash;
1087 		if (h!=='') {
1088 			var i = h.indexOf(name+'=');
1089 			if (i!==-1) {
1090 				var remaining = h.substring(i+name.length+1);
1091 				if (remaining.indexOf('&')!==-1) {
1092 					return remaining.substring(0,remaining.indexOf('&'));
1093 				}
1094 				return remaining;
1095 			}
1096 		}
1097 		return null;
1098 	},
1099 	clearHash : function() {
1100 		document.location.hash='#';
1101 	},
1102 	setParameters : function(parms) {
1103 		var query = '';
1104 		for (var i=0; i < parms.length; i++) {
1105 			query+= i==0 ? '?' : '&';
1106 			query+=parms[i].name+'='+parms[i].value;
1107 		};
1108 		document.location.search=query;
1109 	},
1110 	getBoolean : function(name) {
1111 		var value = n2i.location.getParameter(name);
1112 		return (value=='true' || value=='1');
1113 	},
1114 	getParameters : function() {
1115 		var items = document.location.search.substring(1).split('&');
1116 		var parsed = [];
1117 		for( var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
1118 			var item = items[i].split('=');
1119 			var name = unescape(item[0]).replace(/^\s*|\s*$/g,"");
1120 			var value = unescape(item[1]).replace(/^\s*|\s*$/g,"");
1121 			if (name) {
1122 				parsed.push({name:name,value:value});
1123 			}
1124 		};
1125 		return parsed;
1126 	}	
1127 };

1129 /////////////////////////// Animation ///////////////////////////
1130 
1131 
1132 n2i.ani = n2i.animate = function(element,style,value,duration,delegate) {
1133 	n2i.animation.get(element).animate(null,value,style,duration,delegate);
1134 }
1135 
1136 /** @namespace */
1137 n2i.animation = {
1138 	objects : {},
1139 	running : false,
1140 	latestId : 0,
1141 	get : function(element) {
1142 		element = n2i.get(element);
1143 		if (!element.n2iAnimationId) {
1144 			element.n2iAnimationId = this.latestId++;
1145 		}
1146 		if (!this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId]) {
1147 			this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId] = new n2i.animation.Item(element);
1148 		}
1149 		return this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId];
1150 	},
1151 	start : function() {
1152 		if (!this.running) {
1153 			n2i.animation.render();
1154 		}
1155 	}
1156 };
1157 
1158 n2i.animation.render = function(element) {
1159 	this.running = true;
1160 	var next = false;
1161 	var stamp = new Date().getTime();
1162 	for (id in this.objects) {
1163 		var obj = this.objects[id];
1164 		if (obj.work) {
1165 			for (var i=0; i < obj.work.length; i++) {
1166 				var work = obj.work[i];
1167 				if (work.finished) continue;
1168 				var place = (stamp-work.start)/(work.end-work.start);
1169 				if (place<0) {
1170 					next=true;
1171 					continue;
1172 				}
1173 				else if (isNaN(place)) place = 1;
1174 				else if (place>1) place=1;
1175 				else if (place<1) next=true;
1176 				var v = place;
1177 				if (work.delegate && work.delegate.ease) {
1178 					v = work.delegate.ease(v);
1179 				}
1180 				var value = null;
1181 				if (!work.css) {
1182 					obj.element[work.property] = Math.round(work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v);
1183 				} else if (work.property=='transform' && !n2i.browser.msie) {
1184 					var t = work.transform;
1185 					var str = '';
1186 					if (t.rotate) {
1187 						str+=' rotate('+(t.rotate.from+(t.rotate.to-t.rotate.from)*v)+t.rotate.unit+')';
1188 					}
1189 					if (t.scale) {
1190 						str+=' scale('+(t.scale.from+(t.scale.to-t.scale.from)*v)+')';
1191 					}
1192 					obj.element.style[n2i.animation.TRANSFORM]=str;
1193 				} else if (work.to.red!=null) {
1194 					var red = Math.round(work.from.red+(work.to.red-work.from.red)*v);
1195 					var green = Math.round(work.from.green+(work.to.green-work.from.green)*v);
1196 					var blue = Math.round(work.from.blue+(work.to.blue-work.from.blue)*v);
1197 					value = 'rgb('+red+','+green+','+blue+')';
1198 					obj.element.style[work.property]=value;
1199 				} else if (n2i.browser.msie && work.property=='opacity') {
1200 					var opacity = (work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v);
1201 					if (opacity==1) {
1202 						obj.element.style.removeAttribute('filter');
1203 					} else {
1204 						obj.element.style['filter']='alpha(opacity='+(opacity*100)+')';
1205 					}
1206 				} else {
1207 					value = new String(work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v)+(work.unit!=null ? work.unit : '');
1208 					obj.element.style[work.property]=value;
1209 				}
1210 				if (place==1) {
1211 					work.finished = true;
1212 					if (work.delegate && work.delegate.onComplete) {
1213 						window.setTimeout(work.delegate.onComplete);
1214 					} else if (work.delegate && work.delegate.hideOnComplete) {
1215 						obj.element.style.display='none';
1216 					}
1217 				}
1218 			};
1219 		}
1220 	}
1221 	if (next) {
1222 		window.setTimeout(function() {
1223 			n2i.animation.render();
1224 		},0);
1225 	} else {
1226 		this.running = false;
1227 	}
1228 }
1229 
1230 n2i.animation.parseStyle = function(value) {
1231 	var parsed = {type:null,value:null,unit:null};
1232 	var match;
1233 	if (!n2i.isDefined(value)) {
1234 		return parsed;
1235 	} else if (!isNaN(value)) {
1236 		parsed.value=parseFloat(value);
1237 	} else if (match=value.match(/([\-]?[0-9\.]+)(px|pt|%)/)) {
1238 		parsed.type = 'length';
1239 		parsed.value = parseFloat(match[1]);
1240 		parsed.unit = match[2];
1241 	} else if (match=value.match(/rgb\(([0-9]+),[ ]?([0-9]+),[ ]?([0-9]+)\)/)) {
1242 		parsed.type = 'color';
1243 		parsed.value = {
1244 			red:parseInt(match[1]),
1245 			green:parseInt(match[2]),
1246 			blue:parseInt(match[3])
1247 		};
1248 	} else {
1249 		var color = new n2i.Color(value);
1250 		if (color.ok) {
1251 			parsed.value = {
1252 				red:color.r,
1253 				green:color.g,
1254 				blue:color.b
1255 			};
1256 		}
1257 	}
1258 	return parsed;
1259 }
1260 
1261 ///////////////////////////// Item ///////////////////////////////
1262 
1263 n2i.animation.Item = function(element) {
1264 	this.element = element;
1265 	this.work = [];
1266 }
1267 
1268 n2i.animation.Item.prototype.animate = function(from,to,property,duration,delegate) {
1269 	var css = true;
1270 	if (property=='scrollLeft' || property=='scrollTop') {
1271 		css = false;
1272 	}
1273 	
1274 	var work = this.getWork(css ? n2i.camelize(property) : property);
1275 	work.delegate = delegate;
1276 	work.finished = false;
1277 	work.css = css;
1278 	if (from!=null) {
1279 		work.from = from;
1280 	} else if (property=='transform') {
1281 		work.transform = n2i.animation.Item.parseTransform(to,this.element);
1282 	} else if (work.css && n2i.browser.msie && property=='opacity') {
1283 		work.from = this.getIEOpacity(this.element);
1284 	} else if (work.css) {
1285 		var style = n2i.getStyle(this.element,property);
1286 		var parsedStyle = n2i.animation.parseStyle(style);
1287 		work.from = parsedStyle.value;
1288 	} else {
1289 		work.from = this.element[property];
1290 	}
1291 	if (work.css) {
1292 		var parsed = n2i.animation.parseStyle(to);
1293 		work.to = parsed.value;
1294 		work.unit = parsed.unit;
1295 	} else {
1296 		work.to = to;
1297 		work.unit = null;
1298 	}
1299 	work.start = new Date().getTime();
1300 	if (delegate && delegate.delay) work.start+=delegate.delay;
1301 	work.end = work.start+duration;
1302 	n2i.animation.start();
1303 }
1304 
1305 n2i.animation.TRANSFORM = n2i.browser.gecko ? 'MozTransform' : 'WebkitTransform';
1306 
1307 n2i.animation.Item.parseTransform = function(value,element) {
1308 	var result = {};
1309 	var rotateReg = /rotate\(([0-9\.]+)([a-z]+)\)/i;
1310 	var rotate = value.match(rotateReg);
1311 	if (rotate) {
1312 		var from = 0;
1313 		if (element.style[n2i.animation.TRANSFORM]) {
1314 			var fromMatch = element.style[n2i.animation.TRANSFORM].match(rotateReg);
1315 			if (fromMatch) {
1316 				from = parseFloat(fromMatch[1]);
1317 			}
1318 		}
1319 		result.rotate = {from:from,to:parseFloat(rotate[1]),unit:rotate[2]};
1320 	}
1321 	var scaleReg = /scale\(([0-9\.]+)\)/i;
1322 	var scale = value.match(scaleReg);
1323 	if (scale) {
1324 		var from = 1;
1325 		if (element.style[n2i.animation.TRANSFORM]) {
1326 			var fromMatch = element.style[n2i.animation.TRANSFORM].match(scaleReg);
1327 			if (fromMatch) {
1328 				from = parseFloat(fromMatch[1]);
1329 			}
1330 		}
1331 		result.scale = {from:from,to:parseFloat(scale[1])};
1332 	}
1333 	
1334 	return result;
1335 }

1337 n2i.animation.Item.prototype.getIEOpacity = function(element) {
1338 	var filter = n2i.getStyle(element,'filter').toLowerCase();
1339 	var match;
1340 	if (match = filter.match(/opacity=([0-9]+)/)) {
1341 		return parseFloat(match[1])/100;
1342 	} else {
1343 		return 1;
1344 	}
1345 }

1347 n2i.animation.Item.prototype.getWork = function(property) {
1348 	for (var i=0; i < this.work.length; i++) {
1349 		if (this.work[i].property==property) {
1350 			return this.work[i];
1351 		}
1352 	};
1353 	var work = {property:property};
1354 	this.work[this.work.length] = work;
1355 	return work;
1356 }

1360 n2i.animation.Loop = function(recipe) {
1361 	this.recipe = recipe;
1362 	this.position = -1;
1363 	this.running = false;
1364 }
1365 
1366 n2i.animation.Loop.prototype.next = function() {
1367 	this.position++;
1368 	if (this.position>=this.recipe.length) {
1369 		this.position = 0;
1370 	}
1371 	var item = this.recipe[this.position];
1372 	if (typeof(item)=='function') {
1373 		item();
1374 	} else if (item.element) {
1375 		n2i.ani(item.element,item.property,item.value,item.duration,{ease:item.ease});
1376 	}
1377 	var self = this;
1378 	var time = item.duration || 0;
1379 	window.setTimeout(function() {self.next()},time);
1380 }
1381 
1382 n2i.animation.Loop.prototype.start = function() {
1383 	this.running=true;
1384 	this.next();
1385 }

1557     for (var key in simple_colors) {
1558         if (color_string == key) {
1559             color_string = simple_colors[key];
1560         }
1561     }
1562     // emd of simple type-in colors
1563 
1564     // array of color definition objects
1565     var color_defs = [
1566         {
1567             re: /^rgb\((\d{1,3}),\s*(\d{1,3}),\s*(\d{1,3})\)$/,
1568             example: ['rgb(123, 234, 45)', 'rgb(255,234,245)'],
1569             process: function (bits){
1570                 return [
1571                     parseInt(bits[1]),
1572                     parseInt(bits[2]),
1573                     parseInt(bits[3])
1574                 ];
1575             }
1576         },
1577         {
1578             re: /^(\w{2})(\w{2})(\w{2})$/,
1579             example: ['#00ff00', '336699'],
1580             process: function (bits){
1581                 return [
1582                     parseInt(bits[1], 16),
1583                     parseInt(bits[2], 16),
1584                     parseInt(bits[3], 16)
1585                 ];
1586             }
1587         },
1588         {
1589             re: /^(\w{1})(\w{1})(\w{1})$/,
1590             example: ['#fb0', 'f0f'],
1591             process: function (bits){
1592                 return [
1593                     parseInt(bits[1] + bits[1], 16),
1594                     parseInt(bits[2] + bits[2], 16),
1595                     parseInt(bits[3] + bits[3], 16)
1596                 ];
1597             }
1598         }
1599     ];
1600 
1601     // search through the definitions to find a match
1602     for (var i = 0; i < color_defs.length; i++) {
1603         var re = color_defs[i].re;
1604         var processor = color_defs[i].process;
1605         var bits = re.exec(color_string);
1606         if (bits) {
1607             channels = processor(bits);
1608             this.r = channels[0];
1609             this.g = channels[1];
1610             this.b = channels[2];
1611             this.ok = true;
1612         }
1613 
1614     }
1615 
1616     // validate/cleanup values
1617     this.r = (this.r < 0 || isNaN(this.r)) ? 0 : ((this.r > 255) ? 255 : this.r);
1618     this.g = (this.g < 0 || isNaN(this.g)) ? 0 : ((this.g > 255) ? 255 : this.g);
1619     this.b = (this.b < 0 || isNaN(this.b)) ? 0 : ((this.b > 255) ? 255 : this.b);
1620 
1621     // some getters
1622     this.toRGB = function () {
1623         return 'rgb(' + this.r + ', ' + this.g + ', ' + this.b + ')';
1624     }
1625     this.toHex = function () {
1626         var r = this.r.toString(16);
1627         var g = this.g.toString(16);
1628         var b = this.b.toString(16);
1629         if (r.length == 1) r = '0' + r;
1630         if (g.length == 1) g = '0' + g;
1631         if (b.length == 1) b = '0' + b;
1632         return '#' + r + g + b;
1633     }

1638 /** @namespace */
1639 n2i.ease = {
1640 	slowFastSlow : function(val) {
1641 		var a = 1.6;
1642 		var b = 1.4;
1643 		return -1*Math.pow(Math.cos((Math.PI/2)*Math.pow(val,a)),Math.pow(Math.PI,b))+1;
1644 	},
1645 	fastSlow : function(val) {
1646 		var a = .5;
1647 		var b = .7
1648 		return -1*Math.pow(Math.cos((Math.PI/2)*Math.pow(val,a)),Math.pow(Math.PI,b))+1;
1649 	},
1650 	elastic : function(t) {
1651 		return 1 - n2i.ease.elastic2(1-t);
1652 	},
1653 
1654 	elastic2 : function (t, a, p) {
1655 		if (t<=0 || t>=1) return t;
1656 		if (!p) p=0.45;
1657 		var s;
1658 		if (!a || a < 1) {
1659 			a=1;
1660 			s=p/4;
1661 		} else {
1662 			s = p/(2*Math.PI) * Math.asin (1/a);
1663 		}
1664 		return -(a*Math.pow(2,10*(t-=1)) * Math.sin( (t-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p ));
1665 	},
1666 	bounce : function(t) {
1667 		if (t < (1/2.75)) {
1668 			return 7.5625*t*t;
1669 		} else if (t < (2/2.75)) {
1670 			return (7.5625*(t-=(1.5/2.75))*t + .75);
1671 		} else if (t < (2.5/2.75)) {
1672 			return (7.5625*(t-=(2.25/2.75))*t + .9375);
1673 		} else {
1674 			return (7.5625*(t-=(2.625/2.75))*t + .984375);
1675 		}
1676 	},
1677 	
1678 	linear: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1679 		// summary: A linear easing function
1680 		return n;
1681 	},
1682 
1683 	quadIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1684 		return Math.pow(n, 2);
1685 	},
1686 
1687 	quadOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1688 		return n * (n-2) * -1;
1689 	},
1690 
1691 	quadInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1692 		n=n*2;
1693 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 2) / 2; }
1694 		return -1 * ((--n)*(n-2) - 1) / 2;
1695 	},
1696 
1697 	cubicIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1698 		return Math.pow(n, 3);
1699 	},
1700 
1701 	cubicOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1702 		return Math.pow(n-1, 3) + 1;
1703 	},
1704 
1705 	cubicInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1706 		n=n*2;
1707 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 3) / 2; }
1708 		n-=2;
1709 		return (Math.pow(n, 3) + 2) / 2;
1710 	},
1711 
1712 	quartIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1713 		return Math.pow(n, 4);
1714 	},
1715 
1716 	quartOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1717 		return -1 * (Math.pow(n-1, 4) - 1);
1718 	},
1719 
1720 	quartInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1721 		n=n*2;
1722 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 4) / 2; }
1723 		n-=2;
1724 		return -1/2 * (Math.pow(n, 4) - 2);
1725 	},
1726 
1727 	quintIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1728 		return Math.pow(n, 5);
1729 	},
1730 
1731 	quintOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1732 		return Math.pow(n-1, 5) + 1;
1733 	},
1734 
1735 	quintInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1736 		n=n*2;
1737 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 5) / 2; };
1738 		n-=2;
1739 		return (Math.pow(n, 5) + 2) / 2;
1740 	},
1741 
1742 	sineIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1743 		return -1 * Math.cos(n * (Math.PI/2)) + 1;
1744 	},
1745 
1746 	sineOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1747 		return Math.sin(n * (Math.PI/2));
1748 	},
1749 
1750 	sineInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1751 		return -1 * (Math.cos(Math.PI*n) - 1) / 2;
1752 	},
1753 
1754 	expoIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1755 		return (n==0) ? 0 : Math.pow(2, 10 * (n - 1));
1756 	},
1757 
1758 	expoOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1759 		return (n==1) ? 1 : (-1 * Math.pow(2, -10 * n) + 1);
1760 	},
1761 
1762 	expoInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1763 		if(n==0){ return 0; }
1764 		if(n==1){ return 1; }
1765 		n = n*2;
1766 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(2, 10 * (n-1)) / 2; }
1767 		--n;
1768 		return (-1 * Math.pow(2, -10 * n) + 2) / 2;
1769 	},
1770 
1771 	circIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1772 		return -1 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) - 1);
1773 	},
1774 
1775 	circOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1776 		n = n-1;
1777 		return Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2));
1778 	},
1779 
1780 	circInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1781 		n = n*2;
1782 		if(n<1){ return -1/2 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) - 1); }
1783 		n-=2;
1784 		return 1/2 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) + 1);
1785 	},
1786 
1787 	backIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1788 		var s = 1.70158;
1789 		return Math.pow(n, 2) * ((s+1)*n - s);
1790 	},
1791 
1792 	backOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1793 		// summary: an easing function that pops past the range briefly, and 
1794 		// 	slowly comes back. 
1795 		n = n - 1;
1796 		var s = 1.70158;
1797 		return Math.pow(n, 2) * ((s + 1) * n + s) + 1;
1798 	},
1799 
1800 	backInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1801 		var s = 1.70158 * 1.525;
1802 		n = n*2;
1803 		if(n < 1){ return (Math.pow(n, 2)*((s+1)*n - s))/2; }
1804 		n-=2;
1805 		return (Math.pow(n, 2)*((s+1)*n + s) + 2)/2;
1806 	},
1807 
1808 	elasticIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1809 		if(n==0){ return 0; }
1810 		if(n==1){ return 1; }
1811 		var p = .3;
1812 		var s = p/4;
1813 		n = n - 1;
1814 		return -1 * Math.pow(2,10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p);
1815 	},
1816 
1817 	elasticOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1818 		// summary: An easing function that elasticly snaps around the target value, near the end of the Animation
1819 		if(n==0) return 0;
1820 		if(n==1) return 1;
1821 		var p = .3;
1822 		var s = p/4;
1823 		return Math.pow(2,-10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p) + 1;
1824 	},
1825 
1826 	elasticInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1827 		// summary: An easing function that elasticly snaps around the value, near the beginning and end of the Animation		
1828 		if(n==0) return 0;
1829 		n = n*2;
1830 		if(n==2) return 1;
1831 		var p = .3*1.5;
1832 		var s = p/4;
1833 		if(n<1){
1834 			n-=1;
1835 			return -.5*(Math.pow(2,10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p));
1836 		}
1837 		n-=1;
1838 		return .5*(Math.pow(2,-10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p)) + 1;
1839 	},
1840 
1841 	bounceIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1842 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" near the beginning of an Animation
1843 		return (1 - n2i.ease.bounceOut(1-n)); // Decimal
1844 	},
1845 
1846 	bounceOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1847 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" near the end of an Animation
1848 		var s=7.5625;
1849 		var p=2.75;
1850 		var l; 
1851 		if(n < (1 / p)){
1852 			l = s*Math.pow(n, 2);
1853 		}else if(n < (2 / p)){
1854 			n -= (1.5 / p);
1855 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .75;
1856 		}else if(n < (2.5 / p)){
1857 			n -= (2.25 / p);
1858 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .9375;
1859 		}else{
1860 			n -= (2.625 / p);
1861 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .984375;
1862 		}
1863 		return l;
1864 	},
1865 
1866 	bounceInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1867 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" at the beginning and end of the Animation
1868 		if(n<0.5){ return n2i.ease.bounceIn(n*2) / 2; }
1869 		return (n2i.ease.bounceOut(n*2-1) / 2) + 0.5; // Decimal
1870 	}
1871 };
1872 
1873 if (!Function.prototype.bind) {
1874 	Function.prototype.bind = function () {
1875 	    if (arguments.length < 2 && arguments[0] === undefined) {
1876 	        return this;
1877 	    }
1878 	    var thisObj = this,
1879 	    args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments),
1880 	    obj = args.shift();
1881 	    return function () {
1882 	        return thisObj.apply(obj, args.concat(Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments)));
1883 	    };
1884 	};
1885 
1886 	Function.bind = function() {
1887 	    var args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
1888 	    return Function.prototype.bind.apply(args.shift(), args);
1889 	}

1904 /* ******************* */
1905 /* Constructor & Init  */
1906 /* ******************* */
1907 
1908 var SWFUpload = function (settings) {
1909 	this.initSWFUpload(settings);
1910 };
1911 
1912 SWFUpload.prototype.initSWFUpload = function (settings) {
1913 	try {
1914 		this.customSettings = {};	// A container where developers can place their own settings associated with this instance.
1915 		this.settings = settings;
1916 		this.eventQueue = [];
1917 		this.movieName = "SWFUpload_" + SWFUpload.movieCount++;
1918 		this.movieElement = null;
1919 
1920 		// Setup global control tracking
1921 		SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName] = this;
1922 
1923 		// Load the settings.  Load the Flash movie.
1924 		this.initSettings();
1925 		this.loadFlash();
1926 		this.displayDebugInfo();
1927 	} catch (ex) {
1928 		delete SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName];
1929 		throw ex;
1930 	}
1931 };
1932

1974 // Private: initSettings ensures that all the
1975 // settings are set, getting a default value if one was not assigned.
1976 SWFUpload.prototype.initSettings = function () {
1977 	this.ensureDefault = function (settingName, defaultValue) {
1978 		this.settings[settingName] = (this.settings[settingName] == undefined) ? defaultValue : this.settings[settingName];
1979 	};
1980 	
1981 	// Upload backend settings
1982 	this.ensureDefault("upload_url", "");
1983 	this.ensureDefault("file_post_name", "Filedata");
1984 	this.ensureDefault("post_params", {});
1985 	this.ensureDefault("use_query_string", false);
1986 	this.ensureDefault("requeue_on_error", false);
1987 	
1988 	// File Settings
1989 	this.ensureDefault("file_types", "*.*");
1990 	this.ensureDefault("file_types_description", "All Files");
1991 	this.ensureDefault("file_size_limit", 0);	// Default zero means "unlimited"
1992 	this.ensureDefault("file_upload_limit", 0);
1993 	this.ensureDefault("file_queue_limit", 0);
1994 
1995 	// Flash Settings
1996 	this.ensureDefault("flash_url", "swfupload.swf");
1997 	this.ensureDefault("prevent_swf_caching", true);
1998 	
1999 	// Button Settings
2000 	this.ensureDefault("button_image_url", "");
2001 	this.ensureDefault("button_width", 1);
2002 	this.ensureDefault("button_height", 1);
2003 	this.ensureDefault("button_text", "");
2004 	this.ensureDefault("button_text_style", "color: #000000; font-size: 16pt;");
2005 	this.ensureDefault("button_text_top_padding", 0);
2006 	this.ensureDefault("button_text_left_padding", 0);
2007 	this.ensureDefault("button_action", SWFUpload.BUTTON_ACTION.SELECT_FILES);
2008 	this.ensureDefault("button_disabled", false);
2009 	this.ensureDefault("button_placeholder_id", null);
2010 	
2011 	// Debug Settings
2012 	this.ensureDefault("debug", false);
2013 	this.settings.debug_enabled = this.settings.debug;	// Here to maintain v2 API
2014 	
2015 	// Event Handlers
2016 	this.settings.return_upload_start_handler = this.returnUploadStart;
2017 	this.ensureDefault("swfupload_loaded_handler", null);
2018 	this.ensureDefault("file_dialog_start_handler", null);
2019 	this.ensureDefault("file_queued_handler", null);
2020 	this.ensureDefault("file_queue_error_handler", null);
2021 	this.ensureDefault("file_dialog_complete_handler", null);
2022 	
2023 	this.ensureDefault("upload_start_handler", null);
2024 	this.ensureDefault("upload_progress_handler", null);
2025 	this.ensureDefault("upload_error_handler", null);
2026 	this.ensureDefault("upload_success_handler", null);
2027 	this.ensureDefault("upload_complete_handler", null);
2028 	
2029 	this.ensureDefault("debug_handler", function(msg) {n2i.log(msg)});
2030 
2031 	this.ensureDefault("custom_settings", {});
2032 
2033 	// Other settings
2034 	this.customSettings = this.settings.custom_settings;
2035 	
2036 	// Update the flash url if needed
2037 	if (this.settings.prevent_swf_caching) {
2038 		this.settings.flash_url = this.settings.flash_url + "?swfuploadrnd=" + Math.floor(Math.random() * 999999999);
2039 	}
2040 	
2041 	delete this.ensureDefault;
2042 };
2043 
2044 SWFUpload.prototype.loadFlash = function () {
2045 	if (this.settings.button_placeholder_id !== "") {
2046 		this.replaceWithFlash();
2047 	} else {
2048 		this.appendFlash();
2049 	}
2050 };
2051 
2052 // Private: appendFlash gets the HTML tag for the Flash
2053 // It then appends the flash to the body
2054 SWFUpload.prototype.appendFlash = function () {
2055 	var targetElement, container;
2056 
2057 	// Make sure an element with the ID we are going to use doesn't already exist
2058 	if (document.getElementById(this.movieName) !== null) {
2059 		throw "ID " + this.movieName + " is already in use. The Flash Object could not be added";
2060 	}
2061 
2062 	// Get the body tag where we will be adding the flash movie
2063 	targetElement = document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0];
2064 
2065 	if (targetElement == undefined) {
2066 		throw "Could not find the 'body' element.";
2067 	}
2068 
2069 	// Append the container and load the flash
2070 	container = document.createElement("div");
2071 	container.style.width = "1px";
2072 	container.style.height = "1px";
2073 	container.style.overflow = "hidden";
2074 
2075 	targetElement.appendChild(container);
2076 	container.innerHTML = this.getFlashHTML();	// Using innerHTML is non-standard but the only sensible way to dynamically add Flash in IE (and maybe other browsers)
2077 };
2078 
2079 // Private: replaceWithFlash replaces the button_placeholder element with the flash movie.
2080 SWFUpload.prototype.replaceWithFlash = function () {
2081 	var targetElement, tempParent;
2082 
2083 	// Make sure an element with the ID we are going to use doesn't already exist
2084 	if (document.getElementById(this.movieName) !== null) {
2085 		throw "ID " + this.movieName + " is already in use. The Flash Object could not be added";
2086 	}
2087 	// Get the element where we will be placing the flash movie
2088 	targetElement = this.settings.button_placeholder || document.getElementById(this.settings.button_placeholder_id);
2089 
2090 	if (targetElement == undefined) {
2091 		throw "Could not find the placeholder element.";
2092 	}
2093 
2094 	// Append the container and load the flash
2095 	tempParent = document.createElement("div");
2096 	tempParent.innerHTML = this.getFlashHTML();	// Using innerHTML is non-standard but the only sensible way to dynamically add Flash in IE (and maybe other browsers)
2097 	targetElement.parentNode.replaceChild(tempParent.firstChild, targetElement);
2098 };
2099 
2100 // Private: getFlashHTML generates the object tag needed to embed the flash in to the document
2101 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashHTML = function () {
2102 	var transparent = this.settings.button_image_url === "" ? true : false;
2103 	
2104 	// Flash Satay object syntax: http://www.alistapart.com/articles/flashsatay
2105 	return ['<object id="', this.movieName, '" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" data="', this.settings.flash_url, '" width="', this.settings.button_width, '" height="', this.settings.button_height, '" class="swfupload">',
2106 				'<param name="wmode" value="', transparent ? "transparent" : "window", '" />',
2107 				'<param name="movie" value="', this.settings.flash_url, '" />',
2108 				'<param name="quality" value="high" />',
2109 				'<param name="menu" value="false" />',
2110 				'<param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" />',
2111 				'<param name="flashvars" value="' + this.getFlashVars() + '" />',
2112 				'</object>'].join("");
2113 };
2114 
2115 // Private: getFlashVars builds the parameter string that will be passed
2116 // to flash in the flashvars param.
2117 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashVars = function () {
2118 	// Build a string from the post param object
2119 	var paramString = this.buildParamString();
2120 
2121 	// Build the parameter string
2122 	return ["movieName=", encodeURIComponent(this.movieName),
2123 			"&uploadURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.upload_url),
2124 			"&useQueryString=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.use_query_string),
2125 			"&requeueOnError=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.requeue_on_error),
2126 			"&params=", encodeURIComponent(paramString),
2127 			"&filePostName=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_post_name),
2128 			"&fileTypes=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types),
2129 			"&fileTypesDescription=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types_description),
2130 			"&fileSizeLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_size_limit),
2131 			"&fileUploadLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_upload_limit),
2132 			"&fileQueueLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_queue_limit),
2133 			"&debugEnabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.debug_enabled),
2134 			"&buttonImageURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_image_url),
2135 			"&buttonWidth=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_width),
2136 			"&buttonHeight=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_height),
2137 			"&buttonText=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text),
2138 			"&buttonTextTopPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_top_padding),
2139 			"&buttonTextLeftPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_left_padding),
2140 			"&buttonTextStyle=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_style),
2141 			"&buttonAction=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_action),
2142 			"&buttonDisabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_disabled)
2143 		].join("");
2144 };
2145 
2146 // Public: getMovieElement retrieves the DOM reference to the Flash element added by SWFUpload
2147 // The element is cached after the first lookup
2148 SWFUpload.prototype.getMovieElement = function () {
2149 	if (this.movieElement == undefined) {
2150 		this.movieElement = document.getElementById(this.movieName);
2151 	}
2152 
2153 	if (this.movieElement === null) {
2154 		throw "Could not find Flash element";
2155 	}
2156 	
2157 	return this.movieElement;
2158 };
2159 
2160 // Private: buildParamString takes the name/value pairs in the post_params setting object
2161 // and joins them up in to a string formatted "name=value&name=value"
2162 SWFUpload.prototype.buildParamString = function () {
2163 	var postParams = this.settings.post_params; 
2164 	var paramStringPairs = [];
2165 
2166 	if (typeof(postParams) === "object") {
2167 		for (var name in postParams) {
2168 			if (postParams.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
2169 				paramStringPairs.push(encodeURIComponent(name.toString()) + "=" + encodeURIComponent(postParams[name].toString()));
2170 			}
2171 		}
2172 	}
2173 
2174 	return paramStringPairs.join("&");
2175 };
2176 
2177 // Public: Used to remove a SWFUpload instance from the page. This method strives to remove
2178 // all references to the SWF, and other objects so memory is properly freed.
2179 // Returns true if everything was destroyed. Returns a false if a failure occurs leaving SWFUpload in an inconsistant state.
2180 SWFUpload.prototype.destroy = function () {
2181 	try {
2182 		// Make sure Flash is done before we try to remove it
2183 		this.stopUpload();
2184 		
2185 		// Remove the SWFUpload DOM nodes
2186 		var movieElement = null;
2187 		try {
2188 			movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
2189 		} catch (ex) {
2190 		}
2191 		
2192 		if (movieElement != undefined && movieElement.parentNode != undefined && typeof movieElement.parentNode.removeChild === "function") {
2193 			var container = movieElement.parentNode;
2194 			if (container != undefined) {
2195 				container.removeChild(movieElement);
2196 				if (container.parentNode != undefined && typeof container.parentNode.removeChild === "function") {
2197 					container.parentNode.removeChild(container);
2198 				}
2199 			}
2200 		}
2201 		
2202 		// Destroy references
2203 		SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName] = null;
2204 		delete SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName];
2205 
2206 		delete this.movieElement;
2207 		delete this.settings;
2208 		delete this.customSettings;
2209 		delete this.eventQueue;
2210 		delete this.movieName;
2211 		
2212 		delete window[this.movieName];
2213 		
2214 		return true;
2215 	} catch (ex1) {
2216 		return false;
2217 	}
2218 };
2219

2272 /* Note: addSetting and getSetting are no longer used by SWFUpload but are included
2273 	the maintain v2 API compatibility
2274 */
2275 // Public: (Deprecated) addSetting adds a setting value. If the value given is undefined or null then the default_value is used.
2276 SWFUpload.prototype.addSetting = function (name, value, default_value) {
2277     if (value == undefined) {
2278         return (this.settings[name] = default_value);
2279     } else {
2280         return (this.settings[name] = value);
2281 	}
2282 };
2283 
2284 // Public: (Deprecated) getSetting gets a setting. Returns an empty string if the setting was not found.
2285 SWFUpload.prototype.getSetting = function (name) {
2286     if (this.settings[name] != undefined) {
2287         return this.settings[name];
2288 	}
2289 
2290     return "";
2291 };

2295 // Private: callFlash handles function calls made to the Flash element.
2296 // Calls are made with a setTimeout for some functions to work around
2297 // bugs in the ExternalInterface library.
2298 SWFUpload.prototype.callFlash = function (functionName, argumentArray) {
2299 	argumentArray = argumentArray || [];
2300 	
2301 	var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
2302 	var returnValue;
2303 
2304 	if (typeof movieElement[functionName] === "function") {
2305 		// We have to go through all this if/else stuff because the Flash functions don't have apply() and only accept the exact number of arguments.
2306 		if (argumentArray.length === 0) {
2307 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName]();
2308 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 1) {
2309 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0]);
2310 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 2) {
2311 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0], argumentArray[1]);
2312 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 3) {
2313 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0], argumentArray[1], argumentArray[2]);
2314 		} else {
2315 			throw "Too many arguments";
2316 		}
2317 		
2318 		// Unescape file post param values
2319 		if (returnValue != undefined && typeof returnValue.post === "object") {
2320 			returnValue = this.unescapeFilePostParams(returnValue);
2321 		}
2322 		
2323 		return returnValue;
2324 	} else {
2325 		throw "Invalid function name: " + functionName;
2326 	}
2327 };

2331 	-- Flash control methods --
2332 	Your UI should use these
2333 	to operate SWFUpload
2334    ***************************** */
2335 
2336 // Public: selectFile causes a File Selection Dialog window to appear.  This
2337 // dialog only allows 1 file to be selected. WARNING: this function does not work in Flash Player 10
2338 SWFUpload.prototype.selectFile = function () {
2339 	this.callFlash("SelectFile");
2340 };
2341 
2342 // Public: selectFiles causes a File Selection Dialog window to appear/ This
2343 // dialog allows the user to select any number of files
2344 // Flash Bug Warning: Flash limits the number of selectable files based on the combined length of the file names.
2345 // If the selection name length is too long the dialog will fail in an unpredictable manner.  There is no work-around
2346 // for this bug.  WARNING: this function does not work in Flash Player 10
2347 SWFUpload.prototype.selectFiles = function () {
2348 	this.callFlash("SelectFiles");
2349 };

2352 // Public: startUpload starts uploading the first file in the queue unless
2353 // the optional parameter 'fileID' specifies the ID 
2354 SWFUpload.prototype.startUpload = function (fileID) {
2355 	this.callFlash("StartUpload", [fileID]);
2356 };
2357 
2358 /* Cancels a the file upload.  You must specify a file_id */
2359 // Public: cancelUpload cancels any queued file.  The fileID parameter
2360 // must be specified.
2361 SWFUpload.prototype.cancelUpload = function (fileID) {
2362 	this.callFlash("CancelUpload", [fileID]);
2363 };
2364 
2365 // Public: stopUpload stops the current upload and requeues the file at the beginning of the queue.
2366 // If nothing is currently uploading then nothing happens.
2367 SWFUpload.prototype.stopUpload = function () {
2368 	this.callFlash("StopUpload");
2369 };

2371 /* ************************
2372  * Settings methods
2373  *   These methods change the SWFUpload settings.
2374  *   SWFUpload settings should not be changed directly on the settings object
2375  *   since many of the settings need to be passed to Flash in order to take
2376  *   effect.
2377  * *********************** */
2378 
2379 // Public: getStats gets the file statistics object.
2380 SWFUpload.prototype.getStats = function () {
2381 	return this.callFlash("GetStats");
2382 };
2383 
2384 // Public: setStats changes the SWFUpload statistics.  You shouldn't need to 
2385 // change the statistics but you can.  Changing the statistics does not
2386 // affect SWFUpload accept for the successful_uploads count which is used
2387 // by the upload_limit setting to determine how many files the user may upload.
2388 SWFUpload.prototype.setStats = function (statsObject) {
2389 	this.callFlash("SetStats", [statsObject]);
2390 };
2391 
2392 // Public: getFile retrieves a File object by ID or Index.  If the file is
2393 // not found then 'null' is returned.
2394 SWFUpload.prototype.getFile = function (fileID) {
2395 	if (typeof(fileID) === "number") {
2396 		return this.callFlash("GetFileByIndex", [fileID]);
2397 	} else {
2398 		return this.callFlash("GetFile", [fileID]);
2399 	}
2400 };
2401 
2402 // Public: addFileParam sets a name/value pair that will be posted with the
2403 // file specified by the Files ID.  If the name already exists then the
2404 // exiting value will be overwritten.
2405 SWFUpload.prototype.addFileParam = function (fileID, name, value) {
2406 	return this.callFlash("AddFileParam", [fileID, name, value]);
2407 };

2539 /* *******************************
2540 	Flash Event Interfaces
2541 	These functions are used by Flash to trigger the various
2542 	events.
2543 	
2544 	All these functions a Private.
2545 	
2546 	Because the ExternalInterface library is buggy the event calls
2547 	are added to a queue and the queue then executed by a setTimeout.
2548 	This ensures that events are executed in a determinate order and that
2549 	the ExternalInterface bugs are avoided.
2550 ******************************* */
2551 
2552 SWFUpload.prototype.queueEvent = function (handlerName, argumentArray) {
2553 	// Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
2554 	
2555 	if (argumentArray == undefined) {
2556 		argumentArray = [];
2557 	} else if (!(argumentArray instanceof Array)) {
2558 		argumentArray = [argumentArray];
2559 	}
2560 	
2561 	var self = this;
2562 	if (typeof this.settings[handlerName] === "function") {
2563 		// Queue the event
2564 		this.eventQueue.push(function () {
2565 			this.settings[handlerName].apply(this, argumentArray);
2566 		});
2567 		
2568 		// Execute the next queued event
2569 		setTimeout(function () {
2570 			self.executeNextEvent();
2571 		}, 0);
2572 		
2573 	} else if (this.settings[handlerName] !== null) {
2574 		throw "Event handler " + handlerName + " is unknown or is not a function";
2575 	}
2576 };
2577 
2578 // Private: Causes the next event in the queue to be executed.  Since events are queued using a setTimeout
2579 // we must queue them in order to garentee that they are executed in order.
2580 SWFUpload.prototype.executeNextEvent = function () {
2581 	// Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
2582 
2583 	var  f = this.eventQueue ? this.eventQueue.shift() : null;
2584 	if (typeof(f) === "function") {
2585 		f.apply(this);
2586 	}
2587 };
2588 
2589 // Private: unescapeFileParams is part of a workaround for a flash bug where objects passed through ExternalInterface cannot have
2590 // properties that contain characters that are not valid for JavaScript identifiers. To work around this
2591 // the Flash Component escapes the parameter names and we must unescape again before passing them along.
2592 SWFUpload.prototype.unescapeFilePostParams = function (file) {
2593 	var reg = /[$]([0-9a-f]{4})/i;
2594 	var unescapedPost = {};
2595 	var uk;
2596 
2597 	if (file != undefined) {
2598 		for (var k in file.post) {
2599 			if (file.post.hasOwnProperty(k)) {
2600 				uk = k;
2601 				var match;
2602 				while ((match = reg.exec(uk)) !== null) {
2603 					uk = uk.replace(match[0], String.fromCharCode(parseInt("0x" + match[1], 16)));
2604 				}
2605 				unescapedPost[uk] = file.post[k];
2606 			}
2607 		}
2608 
2609 		file.post = unescapedPost;
2610 	}
2611 
2612 	return file;
2613 };
2614 
2615 SWFUpload.prototype.flashReady = function () {
2616 	// Check that the movie element is loaded correctly with its ExternalInterface methods defined
2617 	var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
2618 	if (typeof movieElement.StartUpload !== "function") {
2619 		throw "ExternalInterface methods failed to initialize.";
2620 	}
2621 
2622 	// Fix IE Flash/Form bug
2623 	if (window[this.movieName] == undefined) {
2624 		window[this.movieName] = movieElement;
2625 	}
2626 	
2627 	this.queueEvent("swfupload_loaded_handler");
2628 };

2661 SWFUpload.prototype.returnUploadStart = function (file) {
2662 	var returnValue;
2663 	if (typeof this.settings.upload_start_handler === "function") {
2664 		file = this.unescapeFilePostParams(file);
2665 		returnValue = this.settings.upload_start_handler.call(this, file);
2666 	} else if (this.settings.upload_start_handler != undefined) {
2667 		throw "upload_start_handler must be a function";
2668 	}
2669 
2670 	// Convert undefined to true so if nothing is returned from the upload_start_handler it is
2671 	// interpretted as 'true'.
2672 	if (returnValue === undefined) {
2673 		returnValue = true;
2674 	}
2675 	
2676 	returnValue = !!returnValue;
2677 	
2678 	this.callFlash("ReturnUploadStart", [returnValue]);
2679 };

2721 Date.parseFunctions = {count:0};
2722 Date.parseRegexes = [];
2723 Date.formatFunctions = {count:0};
2724 
2725 Date.prototype.dateFormat = function(format) {
2726     if (Date.formatFunctions[format] == null) {
2727         Date.createNewFormat(format);
2728     }
2729     var func = Date.formatFunctions[format];
2730     return this[func]();
2731 }
2732 
2733 Date.createNewFormat = function(format) {
2734     var funcName = "format" + Date.formatFunctions.count++;
2735     Date.formatFunctions[format] = funcName;
2736     var code = "Date.prototype." + funcName + " = function(){return ";
2737     var special = false;
2738     var ch = '';
2739     for (var i = 0; i < format.length; ++i) {
2740         ch = format.charAt(i);
2741         if (!special && ch == "\\") {
2742             special = true;
2743         }
2744         else if (special) {
2745             special = false;
2746             code += "'" + String.escape(ch) + "' + ";
2747         }
2748         else {
2749             code += Date.getFormatCode(ch);
2750         }
2751     }
2752     eval(code.substring(0, code.length - 3) + ";}");
2753 }
2754 
2755 Date.getFormatCode = function(character) {
2756     switch (character) {
2757     case "d":
2758         return "String.leftPad(this.getDate(), 2, '0') + ";
2759     case "D":
2760         return "Date.dayNames[this.getDay()].substring(0, 3) + ";
2761     case "j":
2762         return "this.getDate() + ";
2763     case "l":
2764         return "Date.dayNames[this.getDay()] + ";
2765     case "S":
2766         return "this.getSuffix() + ";
2767     case "w":
2768         return "this.getDay() + ";
2769     case "z":
2770         return "this.getDayOfYear() + ";
2771     case "W":
2772         return "this.getWeekOfYear() + ";
2773     case "F":
2774         return "Date.monthNames[this.getMonth()] + ";
2775     case "m":
2776         return "String.leftPad(this.getMonth() + 1, 2, '0') + ";
2777     case "M":
2778         return "Date.monthNames[this.getMonth()].substring(0, 3) + ";
2779     case "n":
2780         return "(this.getMonth() + 1) + ";
2781     case "t":
2782         return "this.getDaysInMonth() + ";
2783     case "L":
2784         return "(this.isLeapYear() ? 1 : 0) + ";
2785     case "Y":
2786         return "this.getFullYear() + ";
2787     case "y":
2788         return "('' + this.getFullYear()).substring(2, 4) + ";
2789     case "a":
2790         return "(this.getHours() < 12 ? 'am' : 'pm') + ";
2791     case "A":
2792         return "(this.getHours() < 12 ? 'AM' : 'PM') + ";
2793     case "g":
2794         return "((this.getHours() %12) ? this.getHours() % 12 : 12) + ";
2795     case "G":
2796         return "this.getHours() + ";
2797     case "h":
2798         return "String.leftPad((this.getHours() %12) ? this.getHours() % 12 : 12, 2, '0') + ";
2799     case "H":
2800         return "String.leftPad(this.getHours(), 2, '0') + ";
2801     case "i":
2802         return "String.leftPad(this.getMinutes(), 2, '0') + ";
2803     case "s":
2804         return "String.leftPad(this.getSeconds(), 2, '0') + ";
2805     case "O":
2806         return "this.getGMTOffset() + ";
2807     case "T":
2808         return "this.getTimezone() + ";
2809     case "Z":
2810         return "(this.getTimezoneOffset() * -60) + ";
2811     default:
2812         return "'" + String.escape(character) + "' + ";
2813     }
2814 }
2815 
2816 Date.parseDate = function(input, format) {
2817     if (Date.parseFunctions[format] == null) {
2818         Date.createParser(format);
2819     }
2820     var func = Date.parseFunctions[format];
2821     return Date[func](input);
2822 }
2823 
2824 Date.createParser = function(format) {
2825     var funcName = "parse" + Date.parseFunctions.count++;
2826     var regexNum = Date.parseRegexes.length;
2827     var currentGroup = 1;
2828     Date.parseFunctions[format] = funcName;
2829 
2830     var code = "Date." + funcName + " = function(input){\n"
2831         + "var y = -1, m = -1, d = -1, h = -1, i = -1, s = -1;\n"
2832         + "var d = new Date();\n"
2833         + "y = d.getFullYear();\n"
2834         + "m = d.getMonth();\n"
2835         + "d = d.getDate();\n"
2836         + "var results = input.match(Date.parseRegexes[" + regexNum + "]);\n"
2837         + "if (results && results.length > 0) {"
2838     var regex = "";
2839 
2840     var special = false;
2841     var ch = '';
2842     for (var i = 0; i < format.length; ++i) {
2843         ch = format.charAt(i);
2844         if (!special && ch == "\\") {
2845             special = true;
2846         }
2847         else if (special) {
2848             special = false;
2849             regex += String.escape(ch);
2850         }
2851         else {
2852             obj = Date.formatCodeToRegex(ch, currentGroup);
2853             currentGroup += obj.g;
2854             regex += obj.s;
2855             if (obj.g && obj.c) {
2856                 code += obj.c;
2857             }
2858         }
2859     }
2860 
2861     code += "if (y > 0 && m >= 0 && d > 0 && h >= 0 && i >= 0 && s >= 0)\n"
2862         + "{return new Date(y, m, d, h, i, s);}\n"
2863         + "else if (y > 0 && m >= 0 && d > 0 && h >= 0 && i >= 0)\n"
2864         + "{return new Date(y, m, d, h, i);}\n"
2865         + "else if (y > 0 && m >= 0 && d > 0 && h >= 0)\n"
2866         + "{return new Date(y, m, d, h);}\n"
2867         + "else if (y > 0 && m >= 0 && d > 0)\n"
2868         + "{return new Date(y, m, d);}\n"
2869         + "else if (y > 0 && m >= 0)\n"
2870         + "{return new Date(y, m);}\n"
2871         + "else if (y > 0)\n"
2872         + "{return new Date(y);}\n"
2873         + "}return null;}";
2874 
2875     Date.parseRegexes[regexNum] = new RegExp("^" + regex + "$");
2876     eval(code);
2877 }
2878 
2879 Date.formatCodeToRegex = function(character, currentGroup) {
2880     switch (character) {
2881     case "D":
2882         return {g:0,
2883         c:null,
2884         s:"(?:Sun|Mon|Tue|Wed|Thu|Fri|Sat)"};
2885     case "j":
2886     case "d":
2887         return {g:1,
2888             c:"d = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
2889             s:"(\\d{1,2})"};
2890     case "l":
2891         return {g:0,
2892             c:null,
2893             s:"(?:" + Date.dayNames.join("|") + ")"};
2894     case "S":
2895         return {g:0,
2896             c:null,
2897             s:"(?:st|nd|rd|th)"};
2898     case "w":
2899         return {g:0,
2900             c:null,
2901             s:"\\d"};
2902     case "z":
2903         return {g:0,
2904             c:null,
2905             s:"(?:\\d{1,3})"};
2906     case "W":
2907         return {g:0,
2908             c:null,
2909             s:"(?:\\d{2})"};
2910     case "F":
2911         return {g:1,
2912             c:"m = parseInt(Date.monthNumbers[results[" + currentGroup + "].substring(0, 3)], 10);\n",
2913             s:"(" + Date.monthNames.join("|") + ")"};
2914     case "M":
2915         return {g:1,
2916             c:"m = parseInt(Date.monthNumbers[results[" + currentGroup + "]], 10);\n",
2917             s:"(Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|Dec)"};
2918     case "n":
2919     case "m":
2920         return {g:1,
2921             c:"m = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10) - 1;\n",
2922             s:"(\\d{1,2})"};
2923     case "t":
2924         return {g:0,
2925             c:null,
2926             s:"\\d{1,2}"};
2927     case "L":
2928         return {g:0,
2929             c:null,
2930             s:"(?:1|0)"};
2931     case "Y":
2932         return {g:1,
2933             c:"y = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
2934             s:"(\\d{4})"};
2935     case "y":
2936         return {g:1,
2937             c:"var ty = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n"
2938                 + "y = ty > Date.y2kYear ? 1900 + ty : 2000 + ty;\n",
2939             s:"(\\d{1,2})"};
2940     case "a":
2941         return {g:1,
2942             c:"if (results[" + currentGroup + "] == 'am') {\n"
2943                 + "if (h == 12) { h = 0; }\n"
2944                 + "} else { if (h < 12) { h += 12; }}",
2945             s:"(am|pm)"};
2946     case "A":
2947         return {g:1,
2948             c:"if (results[" + currentGroup + "] == 'AM') {\n"
2949                 + "if (h == 12) { h = 0; }\n"
2950                 + "} else { if (h < 12) { h += 12; }}",
2951             s:"(AM|PM)"};
2952     case "g":
2953     case "G":
2954     case "h":
2955     case "H":
2956         return {g:1,
2957             c:"h = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
2958             s:"(\\d{1,2})"};
2959     case "i":
2960         return {g:1,
2961             c:"i = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
2962             s:"(\\d{2})"};
2963     case "s":
2964         return {g:1,
2965             c:"s = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
2966             s:"(\\d{2})"};
2967     case "O":
2968         return {g:0,
2969             c:null,
2970             s:"[+-]\\d{4}"};
2971     case "T":
2972         return {g:0,
2973             c:null,
2974             s:"[A-Z]{3}"};
2975     case "Z":
2976         return {g:0,
2977             c:null,
2978             s:"[+-]\\d{1,5}"};
2979     default:
2980         return {g:0,
2981             c:null,
2982             s:String.escape(character)};
2983     }
2984 }
2985 
2986 Date.prototype.getTimezone = function() {
2987     return this.toString().replace(
2988         /^.*? ([A-Z]{3}) [0-9]{4}.*$/, "$1").replace(
2989         /^.*?\(([A-Z])[a-z]+ ([A-Z])[a-z]+ ([A-Z])[a-z]+\)$/, "$1$2$3");
2990 }
2991 
2992 Date.prototype.getGMTOffset = function() {
2993     return (this.getTimezoneOffset() > 0 ? "-" : "+")
2994         + String.leftPad(Math.floor(this.getTimezoneOffset() / 60), 2, "0")
2995         + String.leftPad(this.getTimezoneOffset() % 60, 2, "0");
2996 }
2997 
2998 Date.prototype.getDayOfYear = function() {
2999     var num = 0;
3000     Date.daysInMonth[1] = this.isLeapYear() ? 29 : 28;
3001     for (var i = 0; i < this.getMonth(); ++i) {
3002         num += Date.daysInMonth[i];
3003     }
3004     return num + this.getDate() - 1;
3005 }
3006 
3007 Date.prototype.getWeekOfYear = function() {
3008     // Skip to Thursday of this week
3009     var now = this.getDayOfYear() + (5 - this.getDay());
3010     // Find the first Thursday of the year
3011     var jan1 = new Date(this.getFullYear(), 0, 1);
3012     var then = (5 - jan1.getDay());
3013     return parseInt(String.leftPad(((now - then) / 7) + 1, 2, "0"));
3014 }
3015 
3016 Date.prototype.isLeapYear = function() {
3017     var year = this.getFullYear();
3018     return ((year & 3) == 0 && (year % 100 || (year % 400 == 0 && year)));
3019 }
3020 
3021 Date.prototype.getFirstDayOfMonth = function() {
3022     var day = (this.getDay() - (this.getDate() - 1)) % 7;
3023     return (day < 0) ? (day + 7) : day;
3024 }
3025 
3026 Date.prototype.getLastDayOfMonth = function() {
3027     var day = (this.getDay() + (Date.daysInMonth[this.getMonth()] - this.getDate())) % 7;
3028     return (day < 0) ? (day + 7) : day;
3029 }
3030 
3031 Date.prototype.getDaysInMonth = function() {
3032     Date.daysInMonth[1] = this.isLeapYear() ? 29 : 28;
3033     return Date.daysInMonth[this.getMonth()];
3034 }
3035 
3036 Date.prototype.getSuffix = function() {
3037     switch (this.getDate()) {
3038         case 1:
3039         case 21:
3040         case 31:
3041             return "st";
3042         case 2:
3043         case 22:
3044             return "nd";
3045         case 3:
3046         case 23:
3047             return "rd";
3048         default:
3049             return "th";
3050     }
3051 }
3052 
3053 String.escape = function(string) {
3054     return string.replace(/('|\\)/g, "\\$1");
3055 }
3056 
3057 String.leftPad = function (val, size, ch) {
3058     var result = new String(val);
3059     if (ch == null) {
3060         ch = " ";
3061     }
3062     while (result.length < size) {
3063         result = ch + result;
3064     }
3065     return result;
3066 }

3410 In2iGui.changeState = function(state) {
3411 	if (In2iGui.get().state===state) {return;}
3412 	var all = In2iGui.get().objects;
3413 	for (key in all) {
3414 		var obj = all[key];
3415 		if (obj.options && obj.options.state) {
3416 			if (obj.options.state==state) {
3417 				obj.show();
3418 			} else {
3419 				obj.hide();
3420 			}
3421 		}
3422 	}
3423 	In2iGui.get().state==state;
3424 }
